description:
Sponsored by Hibiki Whisky

At Yamazaki Distillery, the oldest malt whisky-making facility in Japan, Shinji Fukuyo pursues the perfect blend. Fukuyo, the Fifth Chief Blender for Suntory Whisky, shares harmony with the world through subtle, blossoming notes that begin in nature, steep in tradition, and come alive through craftsmanship.

His pursuit of a subtle, harmonious blend is one facet of harmony explored in a new interactive feature considering the concept and state of being through the lens of artistry, nature, tradition and more.

Explore the full experience here: https://businessinsider.com/sc/24-moments-of-harmony 

And learn more about The House of Suntory at https://www.youtube.com/@TheHouseOfSuntory

description:
What does it take to become an athlete at 70, 80, or even 90? Five older Americans prove that it’s never too late to start and that exercising “is the most powerful drug for longevity.” They’ve set goals, built community, and found purpose through sports such as swimming, track, table tennis, and powerlifting.

00:00 – Introduction
01:06 – Discovering Sports
03:46 – Challenges of Aging
08:00 – The Power of Exercise for Longevity
09:58 – Competing Around the World
11:27 – Staying Motivated
13:24 – Building Community Through Sport
16:01 – Credits
